AB  - This paper presents the first empirical examination of the relationship between the average return and the risk of a comprehensive sample of 200 securities which traded continuously from 1966 to 1980 on the Brussels Stock Exchange, a relatively thin equity market. Based on our empirical findings, we cannot reject the hypothesis that the pricing of common stocks on the Brussels Stock Exchange conforms to the Capital Asset Pricing Model.
